snippet.textDisplay:
Jordan and Tana LITERALLY was raised differently. He comes from a two parent, loving family and she comes from a very broken home. I can say the same about me. I was raised with 2 parents, 4 siblings and 2 dogs - until drugs got involved. My once "happy" home turned into my dad going to prison for 5 years for physical and mental abuse against my mommy, my siblings and I - only to come out to 2 of his teenage daughters with babies and my mom falling in love with someone who took very great care of her. I moved out with my baby when I was 16 ears old. My story could go on and on and I could be a "Tana" but I refused to be a "victim". I am a survivor of domestic abuse. I have long since forgiven my dad, my mom and myself. I now have 5 daughters with my husband of 26 years and I must say - my July is my life. I live my life so my kids can tell their children "my mommy and daddy are great parents. They did everything they needed to take care of us. I want to be just like them - if not, @ least a better version of both my parents."
Happy Holidays to all that read this!

snippet.textDisplay:
I never liked Tana, I always saw her as an annoying fake female who does the shittiest of things for attention and enjoys living life as a scandal and a joke. This is the first video I’ve watched of her show or whatever it is, and frankly it made me tear up and feel really bad for her. I had a very bad childhood, my mother dated horrible men, men who beat on me, watched my mom beat and almost killed more than I can count, I was raped and molested, lived in foster homes, moved all the time, including back and forth from Cali and Oregon. Tana is young still, even if she is considered an adult, and I believe her past and how she has lived up to this point has stunted her growth, especially her brain. Because of the drug use and alcohol use, the men, the crazy lifestyle, etc. she has stunted herself to stay as that young girl who lives a dysfunctional family lifestyle, and until she gets sober n therapy and really comes to terms with her past and wanting a better future, then she will stay this stunted person. She hides behind that laugh, those loud screeches, the loud mouth, always having to crack a joke n not take anything seriously. Because behind all that stuff there is a very insecure little girl who has suffered and only wants love and acceptance from others, but doesn’t want to show her real self.
I actually felt heartache and pain for her, this was really hard to watch. I only wish her the best and hope she will one day see that she doesn’t need all that crap she portrays in order to be wanted, loved, accepted. That she will figure out you’re past does not cement your future.
